June 3 at 9:49 AM ¬∑

Jessica Garcia is a 2020 graduate from the Murray site. She plans to attend Dalton State College and work towards becoming an LPN and later a RN. Jessica wants to go into nursing because she has a heart for helping others. She hopes to be the first in her family to earn a college degree. Jessica can‚Äôt pick just one staff member, so she wants to say THANK YOU to everyone who believed in her and motivated her to finish her coursework and earn her diploma. Her favorite quote is from Kim Taehyung of BTS: ‚ÄúWhen things get hard, stop and look back at how far you‚Äôve come. Don‚Äôt forget how rewarding it is. You are the most beautiful flower, more special than anyone in this world.‚Äù
Way to go, Jessica! We‚Äôre proud of your accomplishment!

shared_text:
Mountain Education Charter High School
April 17 at 1:38 PM ¬∑

MECHS is working diligently to provide the safest option for a commencement ceremony for the spring of 2020. Graduation was originally scheduled for May 30th; however, due to the current situation with COVID-19 graduation will either be postponed until later this summer or we will host a virtual ceremony. With that being said, Dr. Lovell and everyone at MECHS would prefer to host traditional graduation with virtual being the absolute last resort. We are working with the University of North Georgia for potential new dates and times. Once we have more guidance from Governor Kemp and the Department of Education, we will communicate that to all of you. Please be assured that graduation will be happening whether at a later date or virtually.

As of the 12th of March 2020, there are no confirmed cases of COVID-19 at MECHS.

Under guidance from Governor Kemp‚Äôs office and Pioneer RESA, Mountain Education Charter High School has made the decision to close all sites the week of March 16th. On Thursday, March 19th MECHS will re-evaluate the conditions of the local area and make a decision on site closures for the following week. As always, MECHS is reflecting the decisions of community partners."

Mountain Education Charter High School Murray will be closed March 16 - March 19, 2020. Please follow our Site Web Page for instructions as to when we will open when our conditions are appropriate.

Students can work from home utilizing online learning during the school closure. Simply go to https://www.mymec.org/students and follow the instructions on the website to WEST REGION Murray Gradpoint. It will be available from 4:00 PM through 9:00 PM, M - TH of next week.

Stay well.

***Dinner, Dessert, Door Prizes***
Students AND their families are invited to join us on TUESDAY, DECEMBER 18th for the MECHS Holiday Celebration! We will have a traditional holiday meal in the cafeteria followed by activities and dessert. Rock Bridge of Chatsworth will be on site with food boxes for families. In order to save your space, students must RSVP at the sign-in desk with their name and the number of family members attending by THURSDAY (12/13).

post_text:
MECHS is offering depression awareness and suicide prevention training as part of the SOS Prevention Program. The program encourages students to seek help if they are concerned about themselves or a friend. MMEC will begin training students on the week of October 22nd.
A packet containing risk factors, warning signs, precipitating events, and a list of local resources has been sent home with students. Parents who DO NOT wish their child to participate in SOS should complete the non-participation form and return it to MMEC to the attention of Danny Dunn, or call the site at 706-686-3500.
